                                        <div class="title">
                                            <span>Is the AR-1 safety certified?</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="content">
                                            <p class="black">The SKULLY AR-1 will ship DOT/ECE certified and is pending AS/NZS 1698:2006 certification. The ECE is the standard safety certification for the American Motorcycle Association, World Superbike Championship, MotoGP™, as well as the majority of independent racing organizations worldwide. With both DOT and ECE certifications, the SKULLY AR-1 has passed the toughest testing standards that exist for motorcycle helmets. </p>
                                            <p class="black"><strong>What about Snell certification?</strong> ECE testing, the most rigorous and up-to-date standard in the world, is a combination of both DOT and Snell testing procedures. The ECE standard is also recognized by over 50 countries. We chose this route because ECE has a few extra tests added in, and we want to make sure the SKULLY AR-1 protects your noggin (and brain) for as many crash scenarios as possible. Research has shown that Snell helmets are associated with a higher rate of concussion and Traumatic Brain Injury in average crash scenarios compared to DOT/ECE helmets.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <div class="title">
                                            <span>Is the AR-1 compatible with my motorcycle?</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="content">
                                            <p class="black">The SKULLY AR-1 is compatible with the 2016 Aprilia RSV4 and the 2015 Aprilia Caponord. We will announce more partnerships in the future via email. If your motorcycle has Bluetooth capabilities for telemetry, the AR-1 might be compatible, but we cannot confirm this right now. For future partnership and compatibility information, please <a href="/#signup">join #SKULLYNation</a> for a monthly email update. We want to make the AR-1 compatible with every motorcycle on the road and we’re working hard to achieve this goal.
</p>
                                        </div>
