                                            <span>Will the HUD obstruct my view while riding?</span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="content">
                                            <p class="black"><strong>The heads up display (HUD) will NOT obstruct your view while riding.</strong> Here’s why:
                                            <ul>
<li class="black">The HUD is just outside your primary field of view (right hand side).</li>
<li class="black">The HUD is seamless, appearing to float in the distance, which means you can always concentrate on the road ahead.</li>
<li class="black">You can quickly see what’s happening behind you or GPS turn-by-turn visual cues because our patented optical technology ensures the that HUD is always in focus.</li>
<li class="black">The HUD’s infinite focus allows you to view and comprehend information instantly without taking your eyes off the road.</li>
</ul>
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </li>
